\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 In preparation for the War Campaign, Draenor has seen a drastic increase in both defense and offense, with much of the former zone now belonging to the opposing faction.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0           * As the conflict between the Horde and the Alliance continues unabated, all players will now find themselves with all of their assigned starting zones set at their initial preferences, with a single "accept" button for the entire campaign.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0           * Learn more about how the War Campaign will work in our blog titled: Patch 8.2.5 \endash  The Alliance Vs. The Horde: The Alliance Wins!}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0           * Additionally, for those realms that did not choose to participate in the War Campaign, players will now be able to opt out of the conflict by visiting their respective Troll, Gnome, or Orc camps and accepting the "Defend" tab.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0           * The "Forbearance" option can also be selected while in a raid, and will cause the offending race to be excused from the conflict.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0           * The Gnomish Racial "Hardiness" ability is now noted in the combat log, and can be seen by both the tank and the healer.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0           * The "Gnomish Overpower" ability is now properly penalized when used.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0           * The "Might Of The Many" achievement for obtaining 5 PvP trinkets has been reset to award rank 3 gear.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0           * The "Unbridled Fury" achievement for obtaining 100 non-combat pet reports has been reset to award rank 1 gear.}
